methods.name: __init__
methods.signature: def __init__(self, prefix=None): self.fd, self.filename = self.tmpfile = tempfile.mkstemp(prefix=prefix)

methods.name: write
methods.signature: def write(self, data): if self.fd: os.write(self.fd, data)

methods.name: close
methods.signature: def close(self): if self.fd: os.close(self.fd)

methods.name: cleanup
methods.signature: def cleanup(self): if self.fd: self.close()

methods.name: __init__
methods.signature: def __init__( self, extensionDir,

methods.name: mobile
methods.signature: def mobile(self): return self._mobile

methods.name: mobile
methods.signature: def mobile(self, value): self._mobile = value self.synctype = "desktop" if not self._mobile else "mobile"

methods.name: log
methods.signature: def log(self, msg, printToConsole=False): """Appends a string to the logfile"""

methods.name: writeToResultFile
methods.signature: def writeToResultFile(self, postdata, body=None, sendTo=["crossweave@mozilla.com"]): """Writes results to test file"""

methods.name: _zip_add_file
methods.signature: def _zip_add_file(self, zip, file, rootDir): zip.write(os.path.join(rootDir, file), file)

methods.name: _zip_add_dir
methods.signature: def _zip_add_dir(self, zip, dir, rootDir): try: zip.write(os.path.join(rootDir, dir), dir)

methods.name: handle_phase_failure
methods.signature: def handle_phase_failure(self, profiles): for profile in profiles: self.log("\nDumping sync log for profile %s\n" % profiles[profile].profile)

methods.name: run_single_test
methods.signature: def run_single_test(self, testdir, testname): testpath = os.path.join(testdir, testname) self.log("Running test %s\n" % testname, True)

methods.name: update_preferences
methods.signature: def update_preferences(self): self.preferences = self.default_preferences.copy()

methods.name: run_tests
methods.signature: def run_tests(self): # delete the logfile if it already exists if os.access(self.logfile, os.F_OK):

methods.name: run_test_group
methods.signature: def run_test_group(self): self.results = []
